!
! Editor choice for composing messages
!
! examples for choiceEditor
!
! xterm -title dxmail-compose-vi  -e vi %s
! emacsclient100x30-0+20  %s
! emacs -geometry 100x30-0+20  %s
! xterm -geometry 100x30-0+20 -e microEmacs %s
! dxnotepad -geometry 600x400-0+20 %s
! 100x30-0+20 is used to overlay existing compose widget with the editor.
! If any of this doesn't work, check your path, try the command on cmd-line.
!*choiceEditor: 	 emacs -geometry 100x30-0+20  %s
!*choiceEditor: 	 dxnotepad -geometry 600x400-0+20  %s
*choiceEditor:	xterm -geometry =-0+20 -title dxmail-vi  -e vi %s
